---
import '../styles/resume.css';

import HeadMeta from '../components/HeadMeta.astro';
import Sidebar from '../components/resume/Sidebar.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<!-- Source code available at https://github.com/WesSouza/wes.dev/ -->
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <HeadMeta
      title="Wes Souza’s Resume"
      description="Printable resume for Wes Souza."
    />
  </head>
  <body class="resume">
    <Sidebar />

    <main>
      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="title">Experience</h2>

        <ul class="no-bullets">
          <li>
            <h3 class="flex-space-between">
              <a
                class="no-wrap"
                href="https://unqork.com/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="nofollow noopener">Unqork</a
              ><span class="info-right"
                >Staff Software Engineer, <span class="no-wrap"
                  >Sep 2020&ndash;May 2025</span
                ></span
              >
            </h3>

            <ul>
              <li>
                Led teams and collaborated with stakeholders to plan and deliver
                new products and enhancements to existing platform areas.
              </li>
              <li>
                Led an initiative to improve platform component accessibility,
                focusing on assistive technologies, keyboard navigation,
                readability, and more.
              </li>
              <li>
                Led the refactoring of a real-time analysis tool, optimizing
                performance for both the front end and back end. This involved
                effective React state management and a simplified algorithm
                written for Node.js, exposed as a GraphQL service.
              </li>
              <li>
                Contributed new components, changes, and complex refactors to
                the company&rsquo;s design system library, utilizing React,
                Storybook, and AG Grid.
              </li>
              <li>
                Led multiple internal task forces to enhance the
                platform&rsquo;s development experience and improve build
                quality. These efforts included using Yarn and Webpack, and
                comprehensive documentation.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h3 class="flex-space-between">
              <a
                class="no-wrap"
                href="https://work.co/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="nofollow">Work & Co</a
              ><span class="info-right"
                >Senior Developer, <span class="no-wrap"
                  >Sep 2016&ndash;Aug 2020</span
                ></span
              >
            </h3>

            <ul>
              <li>
                Led the state data modeling, overall state management, and
                project architecture on a React project building a
                touch-screen-based project.
              </li>
              <li>
                Led the API contract, state data modeling, and overall state
                management on a React Native project for a large restaurant
                chain, using RESTful endpoints, Redux, and Redux Saga.
              </li>
              <li>
                Built a component-based solution compatible with the constraints
                of the client’s CMS and e-commerce platform, allowing use of
                modern React for Aesop’s redesigned web experience.
              </li>
              <li>
                Contributed with React component development, modern CSS styling
                using PostCSS, and state management using Redux or GraphQL on a
                handful of projects.
              </li>
              <li>
                Mentored teammates on back end development and best practices
                while developing mock API services using Node.js.
              </li>
              <li>
                Created and managed an internal email newsletter to highlight
                people’s work, learnings, and shared content, and promote a
                better community.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>

          <li class="page-break">
            <h3 class="flex-space-between">
              <a
                class="no-wrap"
                href="https://www.booking.com/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="nofollow">Booking.com</a
              >
              <span class="info-right"
                >Client-side developer, <span class="no-wrap"
                  >May 2014&ndash;Sep 2016</span
                ></span
              >
            </h3>
            <ul>
              <li>
                Led a complete refactor of the website search boxes, including
                libraries used to autocomplete locations, aiming to reduce
                complexity and dependency on outdated jQuery UI plugins.
              </li>
              <li>
                Developed the design system components used on the Booking.com
                for Business application.
              </li>
              <li>
                Designed and developed a component-based system that aimed to
                better organize the scattered HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files
                the website was based on, improving the developer experience and
                velocity.
              </li>
              <li>
                Mentored interns on career development inside the company.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h3 class="flex-space-between">
              <a
                class="no-wrap"
                href="https://sprinklr.com/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="nofollow noopener">Sprinklr</a
              >
              <div class="info-right">
                Front-end engineer, <span class="no-wrap"
                  >May 2013&ndash;April 2014</span
                >
              </div>
            </h3>
            <ul>
              <li>
                Developed the company website using best practices for HTML
                semantics and SEO.
              </li>
              <li>
                Developed a real-time system using WebSockets for the platform
                to indicate simultaneous users visiting the same resources.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h3 class="flex-space-between">
              <a
                class="no-wrap"
                href="https://www.univision.com/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="nofollow">Univision.com</a
              >
              <span class="info-right"
                >Lead PHP Developer, <span class="no-wrap"
                  >July 2012&ndash;May 2013</span
                ></span
              >
            </h3>
            <ul>
              <li>
                Delivered features for their UVideos video delivery platform,
                including a wish list functionality.
              </li>
              <li>
                Delivered internal features for their content management system
                using PHP.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h3 class="flex-space-between">
              <a
                class="no-wrap"
                href="https://www.mtv.com.br/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="nofollow">MTV Brasil</a
              >
              <span class="info-right"
                >PHP Developer, <span class="no-wrap"
                  >April 2010&ndash;July 2012</span
                ></span
              >
            </h3>
            <ul>
              <li>
                Led multiple projects using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and PHP.
              </li>
              <li>
                Delivered improvements to their Drupal content management system
                using PHP.
              </li>
              <li>
                Developed a proprietary video encoding pipeline for directly
                uploading videos to their own video website as well as YouTube.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h3 class="flex-space-between">
              <span>Connix</span>
              <span class="info-right"
                >PHP Developer, <span class="no-wrap"
                  >April 2008&ndash;February 2010</span
                ></span
              >
            </h3>
            <ul>
              <li>
                Delivered improvements to the company's proprietary ERP system
                used by multiple different businesses, introducing new features
                and providing maintenance on existing code using HTML, CSS,
                JavaScript, and PHP.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h3 class="flex-space-between">
              <span>Netcash</span>
              <span class="info-right"
                >Junior PHP Developer, <span class="no-wrap"
                  >April 2006&ndash;April 2008</span
                ></span
              >
            </h3>
            <ul>
              <li>
                Responsible for the company's financial controlling system that
                processed previous-day payment data sent by banks in order to
                generate intelligence and analytic reports, alerts, and many
                other internal management tasks, using HTML, CSS, JavaScript,
                and PHP.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="title">Education</h2>

        <ul class="no-bullets">
          <li>
            <h3>
              <a
                class="no-wrap"
                href="https://metodista.br"
                target="_blank"
                rel="nofollow noopener">Universidade Metodista de São Paulo</a
              ><div>
                Bachelor in Computer Engineering, <span class="no-wrap"
                  >2010</span
                >
              </div>
            </h3>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
